'''Bab-Prime''' was the precursor to modern-day [[Binary/Legends|droidspeak]] created around [[200 BBY/Legends|200 BBY]]. It was invented by [[Yperio Baobab]], and it allowed for the transfer of a multitude of information between [[Droid/Legends|droids]] and [[Computer/Legends|computers]].

==History==
Soon after its creation, Bab-Prime was changed significantly by a [[Wikipedia:sociology|cybersociologist]] working for the [[Baobab Merchant Fleet]]. By attempting to create a Human-based personality algorithm, the hapless worker instead created a backbone-entangled computer virus. The resulting infection nearly crippled the droid population, with many droids taking on limited personalities and emotions. This tendency resulted in the frequent [[Memory wipe/Legends|memory wipes]] periodically given to droids.

Bab-Prime eventually evolved into [[Bab-Neo]], or "Babno".

